      • executeVisualizerTransition

        public void executeVisualizerTransition(@NonNull Visualizer.PlaybackState pbStateWhilePlaying,
                                        double rate)
        Execute a visualizer transition. This method assumes a forward or backward transition is possible. If rate is positive, a forward transition is assumed. If the pbStateWhilePlaying is NOT continuous, a 'stepping' transition is assumed: the delay is removed and after the transition is finished, the playback state is set to paused.
        Parameters:
        pbStateWhilePlaying - The playback status set during the transition.
        rate - The rate with which the transition will take place. Animation.rateProperty()
